CLass 44 16/09/2025

System Performance Anylysis
============================

# uptime ===> 18:15:32 up  1:14,  3 users,  load average: 0.00, 0.01, 0.05  ====> If the load is increasing then proceed with further troubleshoot

# sar 5 5

User Utilization: who, top ===> If the user is performing nedful activity, we will ge the ETA , kill the process

System Utilization: top, free -m ===> If not not nessasary kill the process, if not extend the swap

swap extention: disk extention
Step1: first identify disk partion
	# parted -l , pvs, cat /etc/fstab
Step2: configure swap file system
	# mkswap <devicename>
	# blkid
Step3: add new swap area
	# swapon -s ===> to view current space
	# swapon <devicename> ===> to add new disk space
	# swapon -s 
	Filename                                Type            Size    Used    Priority
	/dev/dm-0                               partition       2097148 0       -1
	/dev/sdb1                               partition       1046524 0       -2

Swap file extention:
====================
Step1: identify free file system which will not reach maximum value after creating sized files
	# df -h /
Step2: create a sized files in the above file system
	# dd if=/dev/zero of=/usr/local/swap/swapfile1 bs=1G count=1
	# ls -l /usr/local/swap/swapfile1
	# chmod 600 /usr/local/swap/swapfile1
	# mkswap /usr/local/swap/swapfile1
Step3: add new swap area
	# swapon -s ===> to view current space
	# swapon <devicename> ===> to add new disk space
	# swapon -s 
	Filename                                Type            Size    Used    Priority
	/dev/dm-0                               partition       2097148 0       -1
	/dev/sdb1                               partition       1046524 0       -2


I/O Utilization: disk, Nic's

disk: iostat -rn, df -h, ps -ef |grep -i <mountpoints>

nic: ifconfig/ip addr, netstat -rn, ip link show
